latestIgtvVideos.title: How I use Gua Sha for face massage 💆‍♀️
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
-Apply facial oil/hydrating serum before using Gua Sha. It needs a slip to glide on. Never use on bare skin
-Always apply light pressure
-Always make sure that Gua Sha is almost flat on skin while using. Never use on 90 degrees or on any edge
-If possible, use it cold. I like to keep it in fridge.
-Always pull outwards and wiggle at the end of a stroke. Always pull but never push your skin. -The purpose of keeping 1-2 fingers before using it to avoid pulling the skin from other side of your face.
-I do it 5-10 times on each side of the face. 
The idea is to lift your skin, prevent fine lines and trigger blood circulation which helps in de-puffing and getting rid of toxins. I use it 4-5 times a week and feel that using at nighttime is more relaxing. 
I wanted to order from skin gym but apparently it was out of stock then, so ordered from amazon with good reviews & guess it is as good :)
There are so many ways in which you can use Gua Sha, it can be used on neck & back too. For me these 5 moves for face work tremendously well.
